Incident: Javascript Code Detected in Requested URL

Indicators:


Investigation:
  Understanding why alert was triggered:
    Looking at the URL requested and rule triggered, we can see the URL contaned a JS query, which is why the alert triggered. (https://172.16.17.17/search/?q=<$script>javascript:$alert(1)<$/script>)

Traffic information:
  SOURCE:
    Analyzing IP, 112.85.42.13, Looking at our endpoints it is not from the company. Now let's look it up with ARIN Whois/RDAP. Putting it in there, we see this IP is owned by China Unicom Jiangsu province network China Unicom, a Chinese Telecom service provider.

  DESTINATION:
   Analyzing IP, 172.16.17.17, Looking at our endpoints this domain is a webserver for the company. 

  PROTOCOL
    The communication is occuring using HTTPS protocol

Findings:
  After analyzing logs from the outside IP, we see they attempted multiple requests with malicous JS code in the URLS. However all the JS XSS attempts resulted in a 302 (redirect) so we can assume the attack failed. To be sure I looked through the email logs to make sure this was not a planned test. It indeed was not.

Conclusion:
  The company web server recieved multiple attempts at a JS injection with XSS attacks. All of them failed and they were coming from someone using a service provider IP malicously.

Response:
  No escalation needed, blocking IP also not necessary because it's a service provider, it may be used again from a normal user.
